<div id="review_2435738877" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2435738877" />
    <a title="LindaJ^" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4999879-lindaj"><img alt="LindaJ^" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486929124p2/4999879.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2435738877?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LindaJ^" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LindaJ^" href="/user/show/4999879-lindaj">LindaJ^</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780749399894" href="/book/show/884856.A_Dry_White_Season">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4999879-lindaj?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4999879-lindaj?shelf=race">race</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4999879-lindaj?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4999879-lindaj?shelf=africa">africa</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2435738877" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7942126409233556331">An excellent book about South Africa and apartheid from the viewpoint of a white upper middle class man who in middle-age loses his naivety about his government and its treatment of Blacks. He so believes that the court system will correct the wrong, until it doesn&apos;t. He doggedly pursues the collection of evidence to prove that his Black friend and son were tortured and murdered by the police. But the government doesn&apos;t like people like him and repercussions ensue. His family turns against him (</span>
  <span id="freeText7942126409233556331" style="display:none">An excellent book about South Africa and apartheid from the viewpoint of a white upper middle class man who in middle-age loses his naivety about his government and its treatment of Blacks. He so believes that the court system will correct the wrong, until it doesn't. He doggedly pursues the collection of evidence to prove that his Black friend and son were tortured and murdered by the police. But the government doesn't like people like him and repercussions ensue. His family turns against him (except for his teenage son); his colleagues turn against him. But still he pursues the truth.<br /><br />The book was written in 1979.<br /><br />For a very good review see Hugh's at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1807277492?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1">https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a>. </span>
