  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1620367045" />
    <a title="Darren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51183187-darren"><img alt="Darren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1454936698p2/51183187.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1620367045?book_show_action=true">Nov 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darren" href="/user/show/51183187-darren">Darren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/27408568-a-dry-white-season">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51183187-darren?shelf=world">world</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51183187-darren?shelf=guardian-1000">guardian-1000</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51183187-darren?shelf=zz-pc-years-since-birth">zz-pc-years-since-birth</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51183187-darren?shelf=zz-pc-2020-52-few">zz-pc-2020-52-few</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1620367045" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3395496207889220672">True-seeming story of a man who chose to follow his conscience and ask questions about injustice, facing all the repercussions that followed. Thought-provoking, inspirational and well novelised by Brink, but only 3.5 stars rounding down cos (depressing to say) all too familiar type of story arising out of authoritarian regime.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


